-- 
South Africa Mineworkers’ Fund to Grow Investments, Business Day Reports

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-07-01T05:53:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-01/south-africa-mineworkers-fund-to-grow-investments-business-day-reports.html
The South African National Union of
Mineworkers’ investment fund plans to increase its investments
to 3 billion rand in the next two to three years, Business Day
reported, citing Mineworkers Investment Co. Chief Executive
Officer Paul Nkuna.  The MIC’s portfolio is valued at 2 billion rand now, the
Johannesburg-based newspaper cited Nkuna as saying.  The MIC
pays dividends to the Mineworkers’ Investment Trust, set by by
the union, which is also the MIC’s only shareholder, Business
Day said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  